<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9402> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9402" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/10> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "ref. 500" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7682> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7682" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See MRR 2.325, 344, 364. On his coinage when serving under Brutus and Cassius in 43-42, see now Crawford, RRC 1.514-515, no. 500. See Shackleton Bailey, Studies 113- 114.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6519> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6519" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A probable member of this college of priests about 31 B. C. In a number of instances the exact date when a priest became a member of his college is not known, and the conjecture is based on evidence of seniority such as the date of the consulship or some other office. The list of the Quindecimviri is based on Miss Hoffman's observation that the names listed in connection with the Saecular Games in 17 B. C. are arranged in the order of entrance into the college (see AJPh 73 [19521289-294). The names given below are drawn from Miss Hoffman's dissertation, The Membership of the Four Major Colleges of Priests from 44 B. C. to 37 A. D. (Bryn Mawr, 1951, available in microfilm).     The vacancies caused by the civil wars and the proscriptions were promptly filled with partisans of Antony and Octavian or persons who were restored in 39 by the Treaty of Misenum, for in 36 Messalla Corvinus was added to the college as a supernumerary member. See Dio 48.36.4; 49.16.1; cf. 48.43.2." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6184> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6184" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "No title preserved. He served with Cassius against Rhodes and with Brutus in Lycia (App. BC 4.72, and 82), and probably did not survive Philippi. See Grueber, CRRBM 2.481 and 483." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6066> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6066" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proquaestor pro praetore (Cic. Fam. 12.15, prescript) in Asia. Quaestor under Trebonius, he was expelled by Dolabella, and returned to reoccupy the province and attack a portion of Dolabella's fleet with one of his own (Cic. Fam. 12.14, and 15). He continued to serve under Brutus and Cassius in Asia (Grueber, CRRBM 2.481- 483, without titles; see 42, Legates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5984> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5984" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served in Asia under Trebonius (see 43, Promagistrates). Cf. Cic. Att. 14.11.2, dated April 21, 43." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5505> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5505" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 57, Augurs. Elected before Lentulus Spinther." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5501> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5501" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Succeeded Q. Hortensius Hortalus. Elected over L. Domitius Ahenobarbus (Cael. in Cic. Fam. 8.14.1; Hirtius in Caes. BG 8.50.1-3; cf. Cic Phil. 2.4 and 78-84; 13.12; Att. 10.16.5, collega noster; Plut. Ant. 5.1; App. BC 3.7; Dio 45.27.5)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5498> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5498" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A probable member of the college of Augurs on the eve of the death of Hortensius." .
